Bona fide anatomical surface

definition.value: Anatomical surface which marks a physical discontinuity between two or more anatomical structures or is an interface between an anatomical space and one more anatomical structures. Examples: surface of head, costal surface of lung, luminal surface of epithelium, P-face of plasma membrane.

label.value: Anatomical plane

definition.value: Anatomical surface which, as an imaginary plane, bisects an anatomical structure or an anatomical space. Examples: craniocervical plane, plane of pelvic inlet, temporal plane.
